cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.AI

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with the emerging feature of network slicing in future fifth generation networks and proposes a state model for synchronous slice admission control. It could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) as it involves the efficient management of network resources. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it proposes a state machine model for slice admission control. It could also be classified under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as network slicing involves security concerns. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the proposed analytical approximation of the state transition matrix could involve machine learning techniques.
